From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Entrpi <entrpi@proton.me>
Date: Wed, 4 Feb 2026 20:08:02 +1100
Subject: [PATCH] arm64: dts: cix: Add boot-active-sids to PCIe SMMU for bypass

When smmu_pciehub is enabled, the driver initializes all stream table
entries to abort mode. PCIe devices that issue DMA before their IOMMU
domain is attached generate F_TRANSL_FORBIDDEN (0x07) and
F_TRANSLATION (0x10) events, flooding the kernel log.

Add arm,boot-active-sids with the base and common device SIDs for
all five PCIe root ports. This pre-installs bypass STEs for these
streams during SMMU initialization, preventing the event spam.
The bypass entries are replaced with proper translation entries when
device drivers probe and IOMMU domains are attached.

SID mapping (from TRM Chapter 7):
  X1_0: 0x0000/0x0100  X1_1: 0x3000/0x3100  X2: 0x6000/0x6100
  X4:   0x9000/0x9100   X8:  0xc000/0xc100
---
 arch/arm64/boot/dts/cix/sky1.dtsi | 7 +++++++
 1 file changed, 7 insertions(+)

diff --git a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/cix/sky1.dtsi b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/cix/sky1.dtsi
index 0a84662f1d0c6..bb5677e0ea137 100644
--- a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/cix/sky1.dtsi
+++ b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/cix/sky1.dtsi
@@ -668,6 +668,13 @@ smmu_pciehub: iommu@b010000 {
 			<GIC_SPI 80 IRQ_TYPE_EDGE_RISING 0>;
 		interrupt-names = "eventq", "priq", "cmdq-sync", "gerror";
 		dma-coherent;
+		/* Pre-install bypass STEs for PCIe root port and common device SIDs
+		 * to prevent F_TRANSL_FORBIDDEN events during early boot before
+		 * IOMMU domains are attached by device drivers.
+		 */
+		arm,boot-active-sids = <0x0000 0x0100 0x3000 0x3100
+					0x6000 0x6100 0x9000 0x9100
+					0xc000 0xc100>;
 		status = "disabled";
 	};
 
